  "clinicalEvidence": {
    "en": "Chitosan is made commercially from chitin, the structural element in the exoskeleton of crustaceans, and is used as a so-called fat magnet. It has the capability of attracting fat from the digestive system and expelling it from the body so that users can lose weight without eating less.\n",
